<paragraph blockId="9.[191,1440,1337,1397]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,265,1337,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Range</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[277,362,1337,1363]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lewis G." box="[371,513,1337,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref6821" refString="Lewis G. 1888. Histeridae. p. 182 - 244. In: Sharp D, Matthews A, Lewis G (eds.). Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta, Coleoptera, Vol. II, Part 1. Taylor &amp; Francis; London, UK. 717 p." type="book" year="1888">Lewis (1888)</bibRefCitation>
mentions localities in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[894,1025,1337,1363]" country="Mexico" name="Guanajuato" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Guanajuato</collectingRegion>
, D.F., and 
<collectingRegion box="[1137,1216,1337,1363]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Puebla</collectingRegion>
. Additionally, I have examined specimens from the Mexican states of 
<collectingRegion box="[732,811,1371,1397]" country="Mexico" name="Sonora" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Sonora</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[866,970,1371,1397]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
. Also, see “remarks” section below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,1412,1473]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,276,1412,1438]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Habits.</emphasis>
Label data indicate this species has been collected in association with 
<taxonomicName box="[1074,1207,1412,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1074,1122,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Atta</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
ant refuse piles, primarily those of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" box="[366,622,1446,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Atta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis box="[366,527,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Atta mexicana</emphasis>
(Smith)
</taxonomicName>
, and occasionally at lights.
</paragraph>
